{
  "brand": "Panasonic",
  "device": "PROJECTOR",
  "variant": "Panasonic PT-VW/EW/EX/RZ/DZ/DX/DW series (ASCII protocol)",
  "controlType": "RS232",
  "notes": [
    "Source: Panasonic 'Operations and Functions' / 'Serial Communications' RS232 spec for PT-series projectors (PT-DZ870/DZ780/AE4000 reference).",
    "Wire: DB9 cross-over (null-modem). 9600 8N1, no flow control.",
    "Format: STX 'ADZZ;<CMD>' ETX  — STX=0x02, ETX=0x03.",
    "ADZZ is the broadcast address ('AD'=projector class, 'ZZ'=all). Replace 'ZZ' with '01'-'64' to address an individual unit.",
    "Reply: STX '<CMD>' ETX  for queries, or '00<CR>' for ack. Allow ~100-300ms.",
    "Query responses (ASCII): QPW -> '000'=OFF / '001'=ON. QIN -> 'HD1','HD2','RG1','RG2','DVI','YP1','VID','SVD','DP1','NWP'. QSH (shutter/blank) -> '0'=OFF / '1'=ON. QFZ (freeze) -> '0'/'1'. QPM (picture mode) -> 'NOR','DYN','CL1','CL2','CN1','CN2','CN3'. Q$L (LIGHT1 runtime) -> 5-digit hours. QOT (off-timer) -> 0-7."
  ],
